\f0\fs24 \cf0 README FILE\
---------------\
Title: Exposure to Macroeconomic Crises and Risk Preferences\
Authors: Bernard Sarpong and Jun Goto\
Date: November 2025\
Software: Stata 18\
\
OVERVIEW\
-----------------\
This dataset and accompanying Stata do-files support the paper \'93Exposure to Macroeconomic Crises and Risk Preferences."\
The study examines whether exposure to macroeconomic crises during early adulthood (ages 18\'9625) has long-term effects on individuals\'92\
risk preferences, and whether the policy environment at the time moderates this relationship. The analysis combines individual-level\
data from the Global Preferences Survey (Falk et al., 2018) with macroeconomic crisis episodes identified from Barro and Urs\'faa (2008)\
and the Maddison Project Database (2023). The Stata scripts perform data preparation, treatment construction, merging, estimation,\
and robustness checks, including varying thresholds of macroeconomic decline (\uc0\u8805  9% to \u8805  3%). The empirical approach employs OLS and\
high-dimensional fixed effects models with cohort-country clustered standard errors. Required packages include reghdfe, estout, coefplot, and psacalc. \
All datasets are publicly available and must be obtained from the original providers. The code ensures full replication of\
All results, tables, and figures are presented in the paper.\
\
Purpose of the Code\
-------------------\
The Stata do-files implement all empirical procedures used in the study, including data preparation, merging, treatment\
assignment, estimation, and generation of summary statistics and figures.\
